Employee Management System:
Abstract:  The Employee Management System is a backend application developed using Spring Boot that facilitates efficient management of employee data.
The system provides a set of RESTful web services to perform fundamental operations such as creation, retrieval, updating, and deletion of employee records.
Introduction:
In modern applications, managing organizational data in a structured and scalable manner is essential. 
This project is designed to demonstrate the development of a backend system using Spring Boot, following industry-standard practices. 
The application ensures modularity, maintainability, and clear separation between different layers of the system.
System Architecture:  The application follows a layered architecture, which includes:
Controller Layer for handling client requests
Service Layer for processing business logic
Repository Layer for database interaction
Entity Layer for defining data models
This approach ensures proper separation of concerns and improves code organization.
Technologies Used: The application is developed using:
Java, Spring Boot, Spring Data JPA, Hibernate, MySQL / PostgreSQL
Conclusion:
The Employee Management System demonstrates the development of a structured backend application using Spring Boot. 
It highlights the use of layered architecture and RESTful services to build a clean and maintainable system.
